From: Raffaella del Prete <raffaellanz@icloud.com>
Sent: Wednesday, August 27, 2025 2:32 PM
To: Grant Metson <Grant.Metson@tower.co.nz>
Subject: Re: Updates and email only comms

Kia Ora, Grant, On 1 July 2025 I requested a copy of my full claim file und=
er the Privacy Act 2020 (including assessments, communications, and invento=
ries). I understand Tower is required to provide this within 20 working day=
s, which has now

Kia Ora, Grant,

On 1 July 2025 I requested a copy of my full claim file under the Privacy A=
ct 2020 (including assessments, communications, and inventories). I underst=
and Tower is required to provide this within 20 working days, which has now=
 passed. Could you please update me on the progress of my request, or confi=
rm if I should direct this to Tower=E2=80=99s Privacy Officer?

In addition, given that the claim is still progressing, I would appreciate =
it if Tower could provide me with updated copies of my full claim file on a=
t least a monthly basis. This will help ensure accuracy and transparency as=
 new assessments and documents are generated.

I value your assistance on this matter and would prefer to resolve it direc=
tly with your help. Please let me know the next steps.

Ng=C4=81 mihi,

Raffaella


On 1 Jul 2025, at 11:31=E2=80=AFPM, Raffaella del Prete <raffaellanz@icloud=
.com<mailto:raffaellanz@icloud.com>> wrote:


Hi Sasha  and Chris,

I saw that you've recently tried to get in touch earlier today, unfortunate=
ly I was unable to attend your calls.. For clarity and consistency, can we =
please have  all communication from this point forward be conducted by emai=
l only?

I would appreciate your attention to the following:

  1.  Claim Updates and Forward Plan:
Could you elease provide a current update and clear next steps for both of =
my claims: House (C90306048) and Contents (C90306256.This should include an=
y scopes of work, contractor involvement, decisions pending, and expected t=
imeframes.

Also can we agree that you will send updates on both every week so that we =
can ensure alignment and progress?

  1.  Privacy Act Request =E2=80=93 Full Claim Files:
Under the Privacy Act 2020, I formally request a full copy of my file for b=
oth claims (C90306048 and C90306256). This includes all internal notes, rep=
orts, third-party correspondence, scopes, assessments, emails, and any othe=
r material Tower holds in relation to these claims.
  2.  Claims Preparation Costs & Structural Engineer:
I would like to engage a structural engineer to assist with damage assessme=
nt. Please confirm whether Tower requires prior approval of this engagement=
, and provide the policy guidelines or procedures for reimbursement of clai=
ms preparation work.
  3.  Outstanding Expense Claim:
I submitted an expense claim on 26 June, and I=E2=80=99ve not yet received =
any update or confirmation. Please advise on the status of this claim and w=
hen I can expect a response or reimbursement.

Kind regards,

Raffaella Del Prete


________________________________

The information contained in this email message is confidential and may be =
legally privileged. If you are not the intended recipient, please note that=
 any use, dissemination, distribution, or reproduction of this message in a=
ny form whatsoever, is strictly prohibited. If you received this email in e=
rror, please notify me by return email, delete your copy, and accept my apo=
logies for any inconvenience caused. Please note that your receipt of this =
email from a Tower email address does not constitute our consent for you to=
 send any other electronic information to Tower by return, unless specifica=
lly stated otherwise.

